title: Marrakesh Cafe
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Organic, Buffet, Mediterranean, Juice bar, Beer/Wine, Take-out, Middle Eastern, Moroccan, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Was originally veg but reported added chickn to its menu (Mar 2016). Sister restaurant to Warsaw's Tel-Aviv Cafe, est. Jan 2013 at Aleje Jerozolimskie 123a and re-opened here in Jan 2016. Offers Moroccan and Mediterranean cuisines. Modern interior with Moroccan designs. Sample menu items include ecological bread and hemp milk, breakfast sets, tagine with pickeled lemons or spicy with prunes, quinoa tabbouleh, soy shwarma, tofu kofta kebab.
